    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-18T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-18T08:00:00-05:00" n="885"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d885">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8465: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-18T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >February 18, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. The declaration referred to in my 31, February 16, 5 p.m., was signed here
                    yesterday and released for publication abroad after midnight. I shall not
                    telegraph the text unless so instructed.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Minister was quoted as saying after the signature that the modest
                    document which had just been signed would perhaps be susceptible of preventing
                    new complications in the Balkans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
